Memory Puzzle Game
ðŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project is a Memory Puzzle Game built using Python and the pygame library. The game challenges players to match pairs of cards within a time limit. It is a fun and interactive way to test your memory and focus.

ðŸ›  Step 1: Set Up Your Environment
- Install Python
- Ensure Python is installed on your system. You can download it from python.org.
- Install pygame
- Use the following command to install the pygame library: pip install pygame
- Set Up Your IDE
- Use an IDE like Visual Studio Code or PyCharm for writing and running the code.

ðŸ›  Step 2: Write the Memory Puzzle Game Code
- Create a New Python File
- Save the file as MEMORY_PUZZLE_GAME.py.

- Write the Code
Copy and paste the provided code into the file. The code includes:
- A grid of cards that players can flip.
- A timer to track the remaining time.
- A win/lose screen with buttons to Play Again or Exit.

ðŸ›  Step 3: Run the Game
- Open a terminal or command prompt.
- Navigate to the directory where the MEMORY_PUZZLE_GAME.py file is saved.
- Run the game using the following command: python MEMORY_PUZZLE_GAME.py

ðŸŽ® How to Play
- The game starts with a grid of face-down cards.
- Click on two cards to flip them.
- If the cards match, they remain revealed. If not, they flip back after a short delay.
- Match all pairs before the timer runs out to win the game.
- If you win or lose, you can choose to Play Again or Exit.

âœ¨ Features
- Interactive Gameplay: Flip cards and match pairs.
- Timer: Complete the game within the time limit.
Dynamic End Screens:
- Green Background: Displays "You Win!" when all pairs are matched.
- Red Background: Displays "Time's Up!" if the timer runs out.
Buttons:
- Play Again: Restart the game.
- Exit: Close the game.

ðŸ“‹ Requirements
Python 3.x
pygame library

ðŸ’¡ Tips
Focus on remembering the positions of the cards.
Try to match pairs as quickly as possible to beat the timer.

Enjoy playing the Memory Puzzle Game and challenge your memory skills! ðŸŽ‰
